\", \"score\": 0.64746445, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://theweek.com/business/economy/us-steel-nippon-steel-merger-revive-deal-trump\", \"title\": \"Can the US Steel-Nippon Steel merger come back to life? | The Week\", \"content\": \"Trump's arrival in the White House gives Nippon Steel additional reason to complete the merger. The deal is a \\\"key option for countering the impact of tariffs\\\" the Trump administration is imposing on American trade partners, said Nikkei Asia. Trump's proposed tariffs would \\\"significantly change the structure\\\" of steel demand itself, Mori told reporters in an earnings call. One of the president's aims with tariffs is to protect American manufacturing, so \\\"it's clearly better to be inside\\\" the\", \"score\": 0.38964, \"raw_content\": null}]", "error": null}, {"tool": "web_search", "purpose": "Find official press release from US Steel announcing the merger with Nippon Steel.", "args": {"search_query": "US Steel Nippon Steel merger announcement December 18 2023 press release", "number_of_results": 5}, "output": "[{\"url\": \"https://yucommentator.org/2024/02/nippon-us-steel-merger-announced-but-faces-heavy-opposition\", \"title\": \"Nippon-US Steel Merger Announced but Faces Heavy Opposition - The Commentator\", \"content\": \"On Dec. 18, the Japanese manufacturer Nippon Steel made a $13.4 billion offer to purchase Pittsburgh-based U.S. Steel. Nippon Steel claimed that the deal would lead to substantial synergies attributed to sharing technologies and increased expansion opportunities. Yet, soon after the deal was announced, it met strong resistance from powerful political and economic forces. President Joe Biden said that the deal deserves \\u201cserious scrutiny\\u201d due to worries about national security and the U.S. supply\", \"score\": 0.8646883, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/us-steel-sues-biden-over-blocked-merger-with-nippon\", \"title\": \"US Steel sues Biden over blocked merger with Nippon - FreightWaves\", \"content\": \"Nippon Steel is the largest steel company in Japan and fourth largest in the world.\\n\\nThe nearly $15 billion deal was first announced in December 2023. The Nippon deal came after a bidding war by Ohio-based competitor Cleveland-Cliffs Inc.\\n\\nOfficials with the United Steelworkers (USW) union said they favor the company\\u2019s purchase by Cleveland-Cliffs instead of Nippon Steel.\", \"score\": 0.8430832, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://journal-neo.su/2024/10/10/on-the-political-issues-and-problems-related-to-the-planned-merger-between-nippon-steel-and-us-steel\", \"title\": \"Merger of Nippon Steel and US Steel: an important event for the industry\", \"content\": \"Last August, the management of US Steel Corporation (USS), one of America\\u2019s oldest companies, said it was looking for a \\u201cstrategic investor\\u201d to resolve years of accumulated problems. Of all the contenders, by December 2023, Japan\\u2019s Nippon Steel (NS) Corporation had emerged as the favorite, with its promise to invest $14.6 billion in US Steel, within the USA, in the event of a merger between the two companies. Under these circumstances, the deal would in effect be purchase of the latter by NS.\", \"score\": 0.8232293, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://gmk.center/en/news/biden-plans-to-block-the-merger-of-nippon-steel-and-us-steel-bloomberg\", \"title\": \"Biden plans to block the merger of Nippon Steel and US Steel - Bloomberg\", \"content\": \"In early December, Nippon Steel reaffirmed its confidence that the acquisition of US Steel could be completed by the end of 2024 if the deal goes through the proper procedures and is approved by the Biden administration.\\n\\nAs GMK Center reported earlier, Japanese Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba, according to Reuters, sent a letter to the US President asking him to approve the deal so as not to harm recent efforts to strengthen ties between the two countries.\\n\\nTags:\", \"score\": 0.7785319, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.pymnts.com/cpi-posts/us-steel-and-nippon-steel-secure-international-approvals-for-14-9b-merger\", \"title\": \"US Steel and Nippon Steel Secure International Approvals for $14.9B Merger\", \"content\": \"Steel & Aluminium\\n\\nU.S. Steel and Japan\\u2019s Nippon Steel have announced that they have received all necessary regulatory approvals outside the United States for their proposed $14.9 billion merger. The companies revealed this milestone on Thursday, stating that the merger has been cleared by the European Commission and regulatory authorities in Mexico, Serbia, Slovakia, Turkey and the United Kingdom.\\n\\n## Get the Full Story\", \"score\": 0.72465646, \"raw_content\": null}]", "error": null}, {"tool": "web_search", "purpose": "Find the official White House or Treasury statement blocking the merger.", "args": {"search_query": "Biden blocks US Steel Nippon Steel merger January 2025 official statement", "number_of_results": 5}, "output": "[{\"url\": \"https://www.thompsonhinesmartrade.com/2025/01/biden-blocks-the-proposed-sale-of-u-s-steel-to-japanese-based-nippon-steel\", \"title\": \"Biden Blocks the Proposed Sale of U.S. Steel to Nippon Steel | SmarTrade\", \"content\": \"On January 3, 2025, President Joseph Biden issued a Presidential Order blocking an approximately $15 billion proposed acquisition by Nippon Steel Corporation (Nippon Steel) of Japan to purchase Pittsburgh-based United States Steel Corporation (U.S. Steel). Explaining that the proposed acquisition might result in actions that threaten to impair the national security of the United States, the Order requires the parties to take necessary steps \\u201cto fully and permanently abandon\\u201d the transaction\", \"score\": 0.8980626, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://abcnews.go.com/Business/biden-blocks-us-steel-takeover-japan-based-nippon/story?id=117294951\", \"title\": \"Biden blocks US Steel takeover by Japan-based Nippon - ABC News\", \"content\": \"In a statement on Friday, Biden said the decision to block the merger reflected a priority placed on the intersection between the nation's economic and national security interests.\\n\\n\\\"As I have made clear since day one: I will never hesitate to act to protect the security of this nation and its infrastructure as well as the resilience of its supply chains,\\\" Biden said.\\n\\nShares of U.S. Steel fell about 7% in early trading on Friday.\\n\\n## Related Topics\\n\\nABC News\\n\\n## Sponsored Content by Taboola\", \"score\": 0.81770587, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.fastmarkets.com/insights/biden-blocks-15-billion-us-steel-sale-to-nippon-steel-over-national-security\", \"title\": \"Biden blocks $15 billion US steel sale to Nippon Steel over national security - Fastmarkets\", \"content\": \"President Joe Biden has followed up on his threat to block the $15 billion acquisition of US Steel by Japan\\u2019s Nippon Steel.In a statement released early on Friday January 3, President Biden cited national security concerns for his decision, despite US Steel\\u2019s own objections and an inconclusive Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States report.\", \"score\": 0.8088086, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/joe-biden-blocks-nippon-steel-acquisition-us-steel-why-employee-unions-donald-trump-oppose-what-it-means-explained-news-11735882928413.html\", \"title\": \"Joe Biden blocks Nippon Steel-US Steel merger citing Trump and unions opposition. What this means? | Company Business News\", \"content\": \"United States President Joe Biden has officially decided to block Nippon Steel's proposed acquisition of US Steel, sources told Reuters on January 3. According to a report by the Washington Post citing two administrative officials, the official decision is likely to be out today itself.\", \"score\": 0.8003337, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.euronews.com/2025/01/07/us-steel-and-nippon-file-lawsuit-after-biden-blocks-merger-deal\", \"title\": \"US Steel and Nippon file lawsuit after Biden blocks merger deal | Euronews\", \"content\": \"He noted in a statement: \\\"a strong domestically owned and operated steel industry represents an essential national security priority. ... Without domestic steel production and domestic steel workers, our nation is less strong and less secure.\\\"\\n\\nWhile administration officials have said the decision was unrelated to Japan's relationship with the US, this is the first time a US president has blocked a merger between a US and Japanese firm.\\n\\nBiden will leave the White House in two weeks.\", \"score\": 0.7813477, \"raw_content\": null}]", "error": null}, {"tool": "web_search", "purpose": "Find official press release or legal filing regarding the lawsuit after merger block.", "args": {"search_query": "US Steel Nippon Steel lawsuit January 6 2025 complaint", "number_of_results": 5}, "output": "[{\"url\": \"https://www.npr.org/tags/1226103379/nippon-steel\", \"title\": \"Nippon Steel : NPR\", \"content\": \"January 6, 2025 \\u2022 U.S. Steel and its would-be Japanese suitor filed twin lawsuits Monday to defend their $15 billion merger. President Biden issued an order on Friday to block the deal, citing national security concerns.\\n\\nPresident Biden blocked the sale of U.S. Steel to Japan's Nippon Steel.\\n\\nPresident Biden blocked the sale of U.S. Steel to Japan's Nippon Steel.\\nDrew Angerer/Getty Images\\nhide caption\\n\\n### Business\", \"score\": 0.86767644, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.thetrentonline.com/japans-nippon-steel-and-us-steel-sue-biden-administration-over-blocked-takeover\", \"title\": \"Japan's Nippon Steel and US Steel Sue Biden Administration Over Blocked Takeover - The Trent\", \"content\": \"WASHINGTON, DC, USA \\u2013 Nippon Steel and US Steel have filed a lawsuit against the US government, alleging that President Joe Biden improperly blocked a $14.9 billion takeover of the American steel giant to gain political favour with trade unions.\\n\\nThe companies claim the decision ignored established procedures and jeopardises foreign investment in the United States.\\n\\n### Allegations of Political Interference\", \"score\": 0.6643884, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.vcpost.com/articles/128786/20250106/biden-faces-lawsuit-nippon-us-steel-after-blocking-their-15b-merger.htm\", \"title\": \"Biden Faces Lawsuit From Nippon, US Steel After Blocking Their $15B Merger\", \"content\": \"Nippon Steel and US Steel were supposed to break the industry with a $15 billion merger until outgoing US President Joe Biden blocked the deal over national security concerns.\\n\\nIn response, the two steelmaker giants are suing the Biden administration. The newly filed lawsuit was sent to the US Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia, which claimed that the decision was an obvious politically motivated one, and violated the rights of the companies to due process.\", \"score\": 0.6021791, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.pymnts.com/cpi-posts/us-consumers-file-lawsuit-to-block-nippon-steels-acquisition-of-us-steel\", \"title\": \"CPI | US Consumers File Lawsuit to Block Nippon Steel\\u2019s Acquisition o\\u2026\", \"content\": \"A group of US consumers has filed a lawsuit in federal court aimed at preventing Nippon Steel\\u2019s $14.9 billion acquisition of US Steel, citing concerns that the deal could reduce market competition and lead to higher prices for a range of consumer products. The lawsuit, which was filed on Wednesday in San Francisco, alleges that the proposed merger violates US antitrust laws by further consolidating the steel industry, which would likely result in negative consequences for consumers.\", \"score\": 0.5931622, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.nbclosangeles.com/news/national-international/nippon-us-steel-blocked-deal-lawsuit/3595119\", \"title\": \"Nippon, US Steel file suit after Biden administration blocks deal \\u2013 NBC Los Angeles\", \"content\": \"#### By Fatima Hussein | The Associated Press \\u2022 \\u2022\\n\\nNBC Universal, Inc.\\n\\nHis decision comes after the Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States failed to reach consensus on the possible national security risks of the deal last month, and sent a long-awaited report on the merger to Biden.\\n\\n \\n\\nNippon Steel and U.S. Steel filed a federal lawsuit challenging the Biden administration's decision to block a proposed nearly $15 billion deal for Nippon to acquire Pittsburgh-based U.S. Steel.\", \"score\": 0.56489134, \"raw_content\": null}]", "error": null}]

