ver blocked merger with Nippon - FreightWaves\", \"content\": \"Nippon Steel is the largest steel company in Japan and fourth largest in the world.\\n\\nThe nearly $15 billion deal was first announced in December 2023. The Nippon deal came after a bidding war by Ohio-based competitor Cleveland-Cliffs Inc.\\n\\nOfficials with the United Steelworkers (USW) union said they favor the company\\u2019s purchase by Cleveland-Cliffs instead of Nippon Steel.\", \"score\": 0.8430832, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://journal-neo.su/2024/10/10/on-the-political-issues-and-problems-related-to-the-planned-merger-between-nippon-steel-and-us-steel\", \"title\": \"Merger of Nippon Steel and US Steel: an important event for the industry\", \"content\": \"Last August, the management of US Steel Corporation (USS), one of America\\u2019s oldest companies, said it was looking for a \\u201cstrategic investor\\u201d to resolve years of accumulated problems. Of all the contenders, by December 2023, Japan\\u2019s Nippon Steel (NS) Corporation had emerged as the favorite, with its promise to invest $14.6 billion in US Steel, within the USA, in the event of a merger between the two companies. Under these circumstances, the deal would in effect be purchase of the latter by NS.\", \"score\": 0.8232293, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://gmk.center/en/news/biden-plans-to-block-the-merger-of-nippon-steel-and-us-steel-bloomberg\", \"title\": \"Biden plans to block the merger of Nippon Steel and US Steel - Bloomberg\", \"content\": \"In early December, Nippon Steel reaffirmed its confidence that the acquisition of US Steel could be completed by the end of 2024 if the deal goes through the proper procedures and is approved by the Biden administration.\\n\\nAs GMK Center reported earlier, Japanese Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba, according to Reuters, sent a letter to the US President asking him to approve the deal so as not to harm recent efforts to strengthen ties between the two countries.\\n\\nTags:\", \"score\": 0.7785319, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.pymnts.com/cpi-posts/us-steel-and-nippon-steel-secure-international-approvals-for-14-9b-merger\", \"title\": \"US Steel and Nippon Steel Secure International Approvals for $14.9B Merger\", \"content\": \"Steel & Aluminium\\n\\nU.S. Steel and Japan\\u2019s Nippon Steel have announced that they have received all necessary regulatory approvals outside the United States for their proposed $14.9 billion merger. The companies revealed this milestone on Thursday, stating that the merger has been cleared by the European Commission and regulatory authorities in Mexico, Serbia, Slovakia, Turkey and the United Kingdom.\\n\\n## Get the Full Story\", \"score\": 0.72465646, \"raw_content\": null}]", "error": null}, {"tool": "web_search", "purpose": "Find the official White House or Treasury statement blocking the merger.", "args": {"search_query": "Biden blocks US Steel Nippon Steel merger January 2025 official statement", "number_of_results": 5}, "output": "[{\"url\": \"https://www.thompsonhinesmartrade.com/2025/01/biden-blocks-the-proposed-sale-of-u-s-steel-to-japanese-based-nippon-steel\", \"title\": \"Biden Blocks the Proposed Sale of U.S. Steel to Nippon Steel | SmarTrade\", \"content\": \"On January 3, 2025, President Joseph Biden issued a Presidential Order blocking an approximately $15 billion proposed acquisition by Nippon Steel Corporation (Nippon Steel) of Japan to purchase Pittsburgh-based United States Steel Corporation (U.S. Steel). Explaining that the proposed acquisition might result in actions that threaten to impair the national security of the United States, the Order requires the parties to take necessary steps \\u201cto fully and permanently abandon\\u201d the transaction\", \"score\": 0.8980626, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://abcnews.go.com/Business/biden-blocks-us-steel-takeover-japan-based-nippon/story?id=117294951\", \"title\": \"Biden blocks US Steel takeover by Japan-based Nippon - ABC News\", \"content\": \"In a statement on Friday, Biden said the decision to block the merger reflected a priority placed on the intersection between the nation's economic and national security interests.\\n\\n\\\"As I have made clear since day one: I will never hesitate to act to protect the security of this nation and its infrastructure as well as the resilience of its supply chains,\\\" Biden said.\\n\\nShares of U.S. Steel fell about 7% in early trading on Friday.\\n\\n## Related Topics\\n\\nABC News\\n\\n## Sponsored Content by Taboola\", \"score\": 0.81770587, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.fastmarkets.com/insights/biden-blocks-15-billion-us-steel-sale-to-nippon-steel-over-national-security\", \"title\": \"Biden blocks $15 billion US steel sale to Nippon Steel over national security - Fastmarkets\", \"content\": \"President Joe Biden has followed up on his threat to block the $15 billion acquisition of US Steel by Japan\\u2019s Nippon Steel.In a statement released early on Friday January 3, President Biden cited national security concerns for his decision, despite US Steel\\u2019s own objections and an inconclusive Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States report.\", \"score\": 0.8088086, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/joe-biden-blocks-nippon-steel-acquisition-us-steel-why-employee-unions-donald-trump-oppose-what-it-means-explained-news-11735882928413.html\", \"title\": \"Joe Biden blocks Nippon Steel-US Steel merger citing Trump and unions opposition. What this means? | Company Business News\", \"content\": \"United States President Joe Biden has officially decided to block Nippon Steel's proposed acquisition of US Steel, sources told Reuters on January 3. According to a report by the Washington Post citing two administrative officials, the official decision is likely to be out today itself.\", \"score\": 0.8003337, \"raw_content\": null}, {\"url\": \"