ontinue uninterrupted.\"", "error": null}, {"tool": "retrieve_information", "purpose": "Extract key terms and conditions from the merger agreement.", "args": {"prompt": "Extract the effective date, parties, aggregate merger consideration, and any conditions precedent (including regulatory approvals required) from this merger agreement. Use exact language when possible. {{x_8k_20231218_merger_agreement}}"}, "output": "Based solely on the text of the provided Merger Agreement, I have extracted the information as follows:\n\n**Effective Date**\nThe agreement is \"Dated as of December 18, 2023.\" The Merger will become effective at the time the Certificate of Merger is duly filed with the Secretary of State of the State of Delaware, as stated in Section 2.3.\n\n**Parties**\n- Nippon Steel North America, Inc.\n- 2023 Merger Subsidiary, Inc.\n- Nippon Steel Corporation (solely as provided in Section 9.13 of this Agreement)\n- United States Steel Corporation\n\n**Aggregate Merger Consideration**\nEach share of common stock of the Company (\"Common Stock\") that is outstanding immediately prior to the Effective Time (excluding Cancelled Shares and Dissenting Shares) shall be converted into the right to receive **$55.00 per Share in cash** (the \"Merger Consideration\").\n\n**Conditions Precedent (including regulatory approvals required)**\nThe respective obligations of each Party to effect the Merger are subject to the satisfaction (or waiver) of the following conditions:\n- **Stockholder Approval.** The Required Company Stockholder Vote shall have been obtained.\n- **No Legal Restraints.** No injunction or similar Order by any Governmental Entity in the U.S. or any other jurisdiction specified in Section 7.1(c) of the Company Disclosure Letter that prohibits the consummation of the Merger and the other Contemplated Transactions shall have been entered and shall continue to be in effect, and no Law shall have been enacted, entered, promulgated, enforced or deemed applicable